commit.message:
test/types.c: fix build on `gcc-14`

`gcc-14` turned some type punning warning into errors. This caused build
to fails as:

    In file included from /build/mariadb-connector-odbc/test/types.c:26:
    /build/mariadb-connector-odbc/test/types.c: In function 't_nobigint':
    /build/mariadb-connector-odbc/test/types.c:313:49: error: passing argument 3 of 'SQLDescribeCol' from incompatible pointer type [-Wincompatible-pointer-types]
      313 |   CHECK_STMT_RC(hstmt, SQLDescribeCol(hstmt, 1, name, sizeof(name), NULL, &type, &size, NULL, NULL));
          |                                                 ^~~~
          |                                                 |
          |                                                 SQLCHAR ** {aka unsigned char **}
    /build/mariadb-connector-odbc/test/tap.h:652:24: note: in definition of macro 'CHECK_HANDLE_RC'
      652 |   SQLRETURN local_rc= (rc); \
          |                        ^~
    /build/mariadb-connector-odbc/test/types.c:313:3: note: in expansion of macro 'CHECK_STMT_RC'
      313 |   CHECK_STMT_RC(hstmt, SQLDescribeCol(hstmt, 1, name, sizeof(name), NULL, &type, &size, NULL, NULL));
          |   ^~~~~~~~~~~~~
    In file included from /build/mariadb-connector-odbc/test/tap.h:115:
    ...-unixODBC-2.3.12/include/sql.h:649:75: note: expected 'SQLCHAR *' {aka 'unsigned char *'} but argument is of type 'SQLCHAR **' {aka 'unsigned char **'}
      649 |                                       SQLUSMALLINT ColumnNumber, SQLCHAR *ColumnName,
          |                                                                  ~~~~~~~~~^~~~~~~~~~

The change fixes column name parameter to be a char array instead of
pointer array.
bump the VERSION

commit.message:
Fix of SQLCanclel testcase, that would fail in case of RS streaming

on linux.

ODBC-399 Error on the query consisting from the comment only

The fix and updated testcase. Driver can add SET STATEMENT in front of
query to enforce query timeout. In case of comment only it leads to
syntax error, obvilusly. The fix ensures, that query has some "useful
weight".
Also, the patch contains small fix for SQLFetch in case of result
streaming. There was possible, that mysql_stmt_fetch would return the
error, but then C/C returned sql state 00000, and driver treated this
sql state as "no error". That's changed to return still the error.

ODBC-404 Use SET STATEMENT only with servers, that support it

Technically, all currently supported server version supports it. But
people in real world still use some old servers, and it's not hard to
fix.
libmariadb submodule has been updated to v3.3.8

Fixes for MacOS/iOdbc

Testcases and warnings fixes

ODBC-402 Support of NO_BIGINT option with testcase

In addition to OPTION bit MADB_OPT_FLAG_NO_BIGINT, NOBIGINT connection
string parameter introduced.
If option selected, it makes normally SQL_BIGINT column to look like
SQL_INTEGER column.
The corresponding field has been added to the setup dialog.
ODBC-399 The testcase, as it appears now

ODBC-401 SQLCancel fix

Existing tests fail on some platforms, the commit fixes that.

Small improvement in the connection process

If multistatement option was off, the driver would send session tracking
configuration statements in 2 queries, while it's possible to make in
single query.

Changes in tests for xpand

Not sure what's gonna be next, but they've been done. Not complete,
though
Fix Travis build for s390x

Removing dependency on pkg-config from binary rpm

Set policy CMP0054 to NEW

C/C submodule has been updated to v3.3.7 release tag

Plus small fix in the main cmake file

Added dependencies to source rpm

Added some search of C/C lib&header in order to automatically add
dependency on the package containing them to the source RPM. And to
actually improve build using system installed lib - heared could not be
found during compilation in some cases.
Also added search for sql.h for the same reason of dependency on
unixODBC-devel
Added 23.08 to travis matrix

Adding dirver UnixODBC template ini file to installation(RPM/DEB/TGZ)

Adding (post)installation script to RPM and DEB to register the driver
with DM
Adding source rpm build
Moved all packaging, i.e. osxinstall and wininstall under packaging
subdirectory as macos and windows, respectively

Fix of travis script

The driver dilbrary is installed to INSTALL_LIBDIR, rather than to
its mariadb subdir for DEB and RPM.
Ignoring PCDIR for RPM(otherwise we have conflict with other package)
Also changet tests to use driver installation location in case of RPM or
DEB package build, as driver is tested after package installation
Minor changes in pc file

Fix of couple of tests for the case of resultset streaming

Also some fixes for testing in travis with MaxScale, SkySQL and XPand

ODBC-395 The fix and the testcase

There was some old mess with connection object properties for isolation
level, and for setting initial level on connection was used the worng
one, that did not get the value of the attribute. The patch removed that
bogus field and left only one of them.

ODBC-394 Changed use of tx_isolation to transaction_isolation

for server versions starting from 11.1.1
Also fixed one test that would fail if server had only one storage
engine available(and the tests is not about SE's at all).
bump the VERSION

commit.message:
Overriding the problem with c/c requires C99 with older GCC

Fixing issue of lately added tests with old UnixODBC versions

ODBC-392 The fix and the testcase

SQLSetConnectAttr(SQL_ATTR_CURRENT_CATALOG) could work incorrectly if
attribute value length parameter was not SQL_NTS, because the string
could end up not (properly) null terminated after 2 trans-coddings(by DM
to unicode, and by driver to used charset). Using ANSI API is another
pre-condition.

ODBC-391 Only the fix as lower_case_table_names can't be changed for
session.
i.e. the test has been added, but to server has to be in
lower_case_table_names=2 mode to test the fix, otherwise it ensures that
the fix doesn't break catalog functions against server in "normaler"
mode.
The fix adds reading of the lower_case_table_names, and if it's 2, then
it compares table name case insensitively where case sensitive
comparison would be used otherwise.
The problem actually affects not ony SQLStatistics, but almost all
catalog functions, that take catalog and/or table parameter as ordinary
argument.

ODBC-350 The fix and the testcase

It's rather the workaround of the bug in the server - for bit(1) value in
subquery it returns string representation of the value, i.e. '0' or '1'
instead of '\0' or '\1', while reporting the type to be MYSQL_BIT

Update of C/C to v3.3.5

Removed eol'ed server versions from travis

Fix of potential issue found with ASAN

Theoretically connection string parser could read past the allocated
area, if connection string was not null terminated.

Added WITH_ASAN, WITH_UBSAN and WITH_MSAN cmake option to enable

respective compiler options.
Fix of issued found with ASAN on Windows - mostly in tests and one read
past allocated area in the driver(rather harmless), and on Linux - trim
could read before the beginning of allocated area.

ODBC-390 Using SQL_ATTR_QUERY_TIMEOUT leaks memory

The string with new query text in MADB_AddQueryTime was allocated and
then duplicated, when copied to the Stmt structures, but not freed.
